ight:bold !important; margin-top:-90px !important;}', '{"notification":"","thankMsg":"<p>This is a placeholder for the TY message.<\\/p>"}', 0, '', 0, '', 0, 0),
(78, 'Dispute Resolution Services  Three-Party Contracts', '<p>Hospitals/health systems and payors can resolve new or outstanding disputed claims without resorting to litigation through IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;Dispute Resolution Services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We act as an independent arbiter subject to an agreement between the parties. Utilizing its panel of board certified physicians and certified professional coders, the reviews can address both medical and Diagnosis-related Group (DRG) coding issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;reviewers consider the medical record, appeal and denial documentation, their expert judgment along with relevant medical evidence and/or criteria to form the basis of their determinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Commonly reviewed medical necessity disputes involve:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Medical necessity of admission and appropriateness of inpatient level of care versus observation;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Medical necessity of continued care/unnecessary delay in discharge;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Severity of illness; and</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Separate admission based on premature discharge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DRG Validation disputes often include:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Appropriateness of diagnostic/procedural coding; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Sequencing of diagnostic/procedure coding; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Complications/co-morbidities and major complications/co-morbidities; and &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Clinical validation (clinical review to determine if the patient truly possesses the conditions that were posted in the record and whether significant additional resources and/or the length of stay were affected by the diagnoses coded).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The IMEDECS&nbsp;process allows:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">The plan and provider to upload documentation in IMEDECS&rsquo; portal for simultaneous review to determine eligibility of the case and to verify the accuracy of the documentation submitted.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">The case to then be submitted to IMEDECS and assigned and reviewed by a certified coder and/or specialty-matched physician as necessary.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Both parties to monitor case status in real time.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">A final determination to be issued electronically to both parties.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefits of Dispute Resolution Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class="pageList"><strong>Transparent</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:35px; margin-top:-18px;">Both parties can view the documentation submitted. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class="pageList"><strong>Efficient</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:35px; margin-top:-18px;">The entire process is managed electronically.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class="pageList"><strong>Binding </strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:35px; margin-top:-18px;">The parties agree that IMEDECS&rsquo; determination is binding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="left" style="margin-left:-10px;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: left;"><a class="button hollow primary learnMorebutton" href="contact-us" style="font-size: 18px;">LEARN MORE</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'dispute-resolution-services--three-party-contracts', 1, 0, 12, '', '', '', '', '', 3, '', '[null,null]', 0, '[null,null]', 0, '', 2, 0),
(16, 'Wilmad-LabGlass offers the talent, know-how and equipment to do the job right the first time.', '<p>Our skilled glassworkers combine with our experienced&nbsp;engineers to translate detailed specifications into finished products.</p>', 'homeservices1490385208-copy-1490386354', 1, 0, 10002, '', '', 'Request A Quote', 'request-a-quote', '_self', -4, 'Download Brochure', '/uploads/c6b02b38d1fa37857c3505733f72a59c.pdf', 0, '_blank', 0, '', 0, 0),
(69, 'Appeals Services', '<p>Ensuring that everyone receives the care they deserve, while controlling costs, can be a difficult task. This is especially true in an environment that includes changing regulatory requirements, shifting standards of care and the increasing complexity of medical procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>With IMEDECS, you receive quality decisions from the best medical experts. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here, you&#39;ll find services across the spectrum of medicine, including psychiatric, dental and chiropractic cases. Plus, we have attorneys on panel to conduct review of contractual issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your case will be reviewed by a board-certified physician or allied health practitioner with experience&nbsp;treating the issue under review.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;appeals services are performed by specialty-matched reviewers from the most extensive review panel of healthcare specialists in the industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They combine an evidence-based evaluation of the treatment in question with an expert opinion to address questions related to medical necessity/appropriateness, the experimental/investigational nature of a treatment and issues regarding plan coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Organizations choose IMEDECS to</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList" style="margin-left: 18.75pt;">Provide unbiased health care decisions;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList" style="margin-left: 18.75pt;">Meet state and federal mandates;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList" style="margin-left: 18.75pt;">Provide second opinion options for their patients or insured members; and</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList" style="margin-left: 18.75pt;">Evaluate alternative therapies and more.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p class="aboveBulletHeadline">Medical Necessity</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Questions or disputes often involve the appropriateness of hospital stays or the necessity of treatments, services or prescription drugs.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Our specialty-matched reviewers consider all submitted medical documentation, national and health plan-specific clinical criteria or guidelines, health benefit plan language/coverage, prior appeals, and adverse determinations, when relevant.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a sample&nbsp;medical necessity report, </strong><a href="http://www.imedecs.com/sample-app/sample_login.php?errorNo=1&amp;extra=3"><strong>click here.</strong></a> &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="aboveBulletHeadline">Experimental/Investigational</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Expert opinion is informed by an evidence-based approach to the questions related to the experimental status of the proposed treatment/procedure.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Reviews may involve complex diagnoses, disabling, progressive conditions, and terminal illnesses.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Reviewers consider scientific evidence supporting safety, effectiveness and medical necessity of proposed controversial medical treatments and procedures.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Written conclusions and rationale are supported with references from the peer reviewed medical research literature.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a sample experimental/investigational report, </strong><a href="http://www.imedecs.com/sample-app/view_file.php?id=4"><strong>click here</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="aboveBulletHeadline">Coverage Determination</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Coverage for a medical service, procedure or treatment has been denied for contractual versus medical reasons, such as out of network services.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Coverage determination reviews involve appeals where the Certificate of Coverage is interpreted by the plan as excluding the proposed or disputed service.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Reviewers trained and experienced in health benefit contract interpretation will examine the specific situation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a sample coverage determination report, </strong><a href="http://www.imedecs.com/sample-app/view_file.php?id=5"><strong>click here.</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="aboveBulletHeadline">Formulary/Pharmacy Exception</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Coverage for a drug has been denied as it is not on the health plan&rsquo;s formulary list, a Formulary/Pharmacy Exception Review can resolve the case expeditiously and effectively.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Here, reviewers consider the efficacy and adverse effects of the proposed drug compared to the formulary drugs to determine whether an exception should be allowed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a sample formulary exception report, </strong><a href="http://www.imedecs.com/sample-app/view_file.php?id=5"><strong style="transition: all 400ms;">click here.</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<table style="margin-left:-12px !important;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="aboveBulletHeadline" style="text-align:left" valign="top"><strong>For more information, please contact us here.&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: right;"><a class="button hollow primary learnMorebutton" href="contact-us" style="font-size: 18px;">LEARN MORE</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'appeal-services', 1, 0, 12, '', '', '', '', '', 2, '', '[null,null]', 0, '[null,null]', 0, '', 2, 0),
