(74, 'Corporate Integrity Agreement Claims Review Services', '<p>Corporate Integrity Agreement (CIA) settlements, between the government and health care providers who have been the subject of an investigation, allow providers to continue to participate in federal health care programs subject to the terms of their agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have a Corporate Integrity Agreement, we can help you fulfill your obligations related to independent claims reviews.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Our claims review services will help you comply with the monitoring requirements of your integrity agreement by conducting quarterly or annual reviews in a timely manner.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">We maintain a panel of certified professional coders to conduct the scheduled reviews.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">And, if you need more than a coding/billing claims review, our extensive panel of board certified physicians are available to address medical necessity issues.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Let us help you with your CIA claims review needs.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our well-established team of experienced experts is here to help.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<table style="margin-left:-12px !important;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="aboveBulletHeadline" style="text-align:left" valign="top"><strong>For more information, please contact us here.&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: right;"><a class="button hollow primary learnMorebutton" href="contact-us" style="font-size: 18px;">LEARN MORE</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'corporate-integrity-agreement-claims-review-services', 1, 0, 12, '', '', '', '', '', 7, '', '[null,null]', 0, '[null,null]', 0, '', 2, 0),
(73, 'Self Disclosure Review Services', '<p>Health care providers must render care with integrity. Under the federal health care programs, it is the provider&#39;s responsibility to take measures to detect and prevent fraud and abuse activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Providers may make a determination to self-disclose potential fraud to the Office of Inspector General (OIG). IMEDECS recognizes that this decision is a significant one. And we can help with investigations should any potential fraud issues arise. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some potential fraud issues may include:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Medical necessity of the services provided.</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Frequency of the services performed\r\n	<ul style="list-style-type:circle; padding-top:10px;">\r\n		<li class="pageList">Over-utilization</li>\r\n		<li class="pageList" style="margin-top:-10px !important;">Billing for services not provided</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList" style="margin-top:-10px;">Appropriateness of the coding (e.g., upcoding, unbundling)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A Self-Disclosure Review begins with an assessment of a sample of claims to determine how broad an issue is and determines what, if any, overpayment must be reimbursed to the federal program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conducting these assessments generally requires a combination of actively practicing, board certified physicians, certified professional coders, and/or statisticians. IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;comprehensive panel of experts meets this need.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>In the IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;process, we:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Determine a statistically valid random sample of claims to be pulled for review;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Conduct a review of the appropriateness of the services provided;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Review the accuracy of the coding submitted, when applicable; and</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Provide a comprehensive report of its findings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>With IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;Self Disclosure Review Services, you get the accurate data you need to disclose pertinent information to appropriate federal entities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can significantly reduce potential penalty fees and help you maintain a<br class="mobileBreak1" />\r\npositive, government relationship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="left" style="margin-left:-10px;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: left;"><a class="button hollow primary learnMorebutton" href="contact-us" style="font-size: 18px;">LEARN MORE</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'self-disclosure-review-services', 1, 0, 12, '', '', '', '', '', 6, '', '[null,null]', 0, '[null,null]', 0, '', 2, 0),
(71, 'Peer Review Services', '<p>Regardless of where health care is rendered, the quality of care provided is expected to meet or exceed the current acceptable standards of care.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to prevent medical errors and/or adverse outcomes, facilities and/or providers must remain vigilant in meeting industry quality standards. This includes evaluating their performance and addressing any gaps that arise between recommended and actual practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;Peer Review Services help you identify and/or prevent medical errors as well as unintended outcomes by assessing the quality of care that medical practitioners provide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reviews can be focused on one patient/one provider to examine an adverse event or an unintended outcome while multiple patient reviews allow you to compare patterns of practice against the standards of care. A multiple practitioner/single patient review will allow an examination of the quality of care provided during the progression of care that may help to potentially identify systemic issues affecting patient care.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health care providers and payors should incorporate external quality of care review into their peer review processes as a best practice that occurs at any point on the health care continuum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Peer review issues commonly include:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Appropriateness of the services provided;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Appropriateness of the clinical decision making;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Timeliness of the intervention;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Deviations from established standards of care; and</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Identification of never events.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;Peer Reviews can:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Address and/or prevent medical errors and unintended outcomes by assessing the quality of care that medical practitioners are providing;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Improve patient safety, services and care levels;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Enhance internal quality efforts;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Inform ongoing internal credentialing/privileging efforts; and</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Reduce costs and more.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a sample Quality of Care&nbsp;report,&nbsp;</strong><a href="http://www.imedecs.com/sample-app/view_file.php?id=5"><strong style="transition: all 400ms;">click here.</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<table style="margin-left:-12px !important;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="aboveBulletHeadline" style="text-align:left" valign="top" width="70%"><a href="contact-us" style="text-decoration:underline;"><strong>Contact us here for more information and to start your peer review process.&nbsp;</strong></a></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: right;"><a class="button hollow primary learnMorebutton" href="contact-us" style="font-size: 18px;">LEARN MORE</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'peer-review-services', 1, 0, 12, '', '', '', '', '', 4, '', '[null,null]', 0, '[null,null]', 0, '', 2, 0),
(68, 'Why Imedecs?', '<p>With its reputation for quality and established record of performance in the national healthcare industry, IMEDECS is known for objective and comprehensive medical review services... driven by the most experienced panel of healthcare specialists in the industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:15px"><strong>Our Mission: </strong>To provide independent, informed expert medical review services that resolve coverage disputes or evaluate quality of care. Through our medical review program, we are dedicated to quality health care and improved clinical outcomes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="aboveBulletHeadline">Unique Benefits of Working with IMEDECS:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="point-list">\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h6>Receive individualized customer care.</h6>\r\n\r\n	<p>Cases may have different requirements, issues and timeframes. That&#39;s why a member of our expert and experienced team will discuss your specific needs in advance to provide the<br class="mobileBreak1" />\r\n	best solution possible.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	IMEDECS fosters a corporate culture of mutual respect promoting equally beneficial relationships between its clients, the company and its employees.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h6>Access the most in-depth specialty-matched expert review panel in the industry.</h6>\r\n\r\n	<p>Because of our long-standing reputation, IMEDECS attracts the highest quality of medical experts in numerous areas of expertise.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>Physicians, Certified Professional Coders&reg; (CPCs), attorneys, nurses, statisticians, and other specialists nationwide come to IMEDECS for review opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>This means that our review panel includes unsurpassed quality, depth and breadth to handle whatever requests we receive. And your case is pre-screened to ensure that the reviewer has no conflict-of-interest prior to conducting the review.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h6>Comply with industry requirements.</h6>\r\n\r\n	<p>IMEDECS holds a Comprehensive Independent Review Organization (internal &amp; External) accreditation under URAC.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>The URAC accreditation ensures compliance to the industry&#39;s most stringent protocols with respect to internal and external review procedures, quality assurance, confidentiality, and security.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>We are also active members of the <a href="http://nairo.org/">National Association of Independent Review Organizations (NAIRO)</a>.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h6>Get the information you need via online technology.</h6>\r\n\r\n	<p>You can use AccessIMEDECS twenty-four hours a day, seven days a week. This is our user-friendly state-of-the-art online review management system you can access to review your data at any time.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We are here to help you.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feel free to review our various services and contact us with any questions you may have. We also provide customized services to meet your unique needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="entry-page-learn-more">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="small-12 medium-9 columns">\r\n<p style="margin-top:15px; margin-left:15px"><a href="contact-us">Please contact us here for additional information.</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="small-12 medium-3 columns"><a class="button hollow primary" href="contact-us" style="margin-left:15px">LEARN MORE</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'why-imedecs', 1, 0, 2, '', '', '', '', '', 12, '', '[null,null]', 0, '[null,null]', 0, '', 2, 1),
(72, 'Coding Reviews', '<p>To help determine the accuracy of coding and billing, IMEDECS provides comprehensive coding review services conducted by our expert panel of Certified Professional Coders<sup>&reg;</sup> (CPCs). The CPCs have experience with professional, inpatient and outpatient coding conventions. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reviewers consider clinical, billing and reimbursement documentation using nationally-accepted, payor-specific standards and/or guidelines to make determinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Submitted healthcare claims are compared against medical records and governing guidelines to verify that the treatment claimed for reimbursement was actually performed, correctly coded and documented as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>IMEDECS&#39;&nbsp;coding services include:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="pageList">\r\n	<li class="pageList">Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) validation;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Evaluation and Management (E&amp;M) coding;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Appropriate use of modifiers;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Medical record documentation (includes medical necessity review);</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Bundling/unbundling;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Usual and customary review;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Inpatient/outpatient audits;</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">Appeal /binding resolution services in any of these areas; and</li>\r\n	<li class="pageList">In compliance with National Correct Coding Initiative (NCCI) edits and/or other standard<br class="mobileBreak1" />\r\n	coding guidelines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class="pageList">IMEDECS is available to discuss how we can best customize our expertise to meet your needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a sample coding report, </strong><a href="http://www.imedecs.com/sample-app/view_file.php?id=4"><strong>click here</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="left" style="margin-left:-10px;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: left;"><a class="button hollow primary learnMorebutton" href="contact-us" style="font-size: 18px;">LEARN MORE</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'coding-reviews', 1, 0, 12, '', '', '', '', '', 5, '', '[null,null]', 0, '[null,null]', 0, '', 2, 0),
